<h2 align="center">Rexx Stuff</h2>
<p align="left">Rexx is a scripting language used heavily on OS/390 Mainframes
under TSO, ISPF, and sometimes batch work. It also exits in various forms
on Unix, and PC.</p>
<p align="left">Here there is a <a href="Computers/rexxfaq.html">Rexx FAQ
</a>for Rexx on OS/390 Mainframes, and a <a
 href="Computers/RexxStyleGuide.html">Style Guide for Rexx.</a><br>
This FAQ attempts to cover questions specific to Rexx on OS/390, for general
Rexx questions, see the <a
 href="http://www.mindspring.com/%7Edave_martin/RexxFAQ.html">general Rexx
FAQ. </a></p>
<p align="center"><img src="Pics/fishes1.gif"></p>
